FALSE(1)                       User Commands                       FALSE(1)

NAME
    false - do nothing, unsuccessfully

SYNOPSIS
    false [IGNORED]...

DESCRIPTION
    Exit with a status of 1. All arguments are ignored. Useful as a
    placeholder or to force a failure status in a script.

    This is the unmodified GNU coreutils false(1), ported to Horus and run as
    a ring-3 program from /bin/false.

EXIT STATUS
    Always 1.

SEE ALSO
    true(1), hier(7)
